text=(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#9e0b0f align=center:)%0a!!%25white%25The Honorable Gideon Ward%25white%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=15 width=400 align=center:) %0a%25width="400"%25http://imageshack.com/scaled/800x600/405/e82f.jpg%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Age:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 76%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Apparent Age:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 48%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Height:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 6'0"%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Weight:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 190 lbs.%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Profession:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Judge%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Covenant:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) [[Carthian Movement]]%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Clan:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Ventrue%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Public Effects:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Status 3 (Carthian); Status 1 (City); Status 1 (Ventrue); Striking Looks +1.%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Player:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) PresterJohn%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Desk:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) [[GideonDesk|Gideon's Massive Desk]]%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) [[http://grooveshark.com/#!/playlist/Gideon+Ward/92586290 |Gideon's Playlist]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_d.png%0a''Gideon Ward stands at an even six foot, but his presence looms larger.  His square jaw and and short blonde hair mark out a handsome face marred by an unsettling intensity in his pale blue eyes.  Gideon is perpetually dressed for business, typically in old-fashioned cuts with three-piece suits and peaked-lapel jackets.''%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_h.png%0a''Gideon Ward has stalked the streets of Savannah for nearly twenty years.  Genteel and capable, he quickly found a place in Kindred society.  When Gideon is not cultivating his own projects, he serves the Carthian Movement mentoring fledglings, mediating disputes, and clerking with the Senate.  Gideon has become known recently for pushing a social agenda of legal reform.  The proclamations of the Senate and the Prince, Ward says, are not sufficient to properly order society.  Kindred Society ought to adopt proper law for contracts and property, in addition to the Traditions and the old laws fiefdoms.''%0a%0a''In Gideon's mortal days, now nearly thirty years past, the man was an upstanding man from a proud family.  At the apex of an enviable career, Judge Ward sat on the bench of the Georgia Court of Appeals, and was on the verge of an appointment to the Georgia Supreme Court.  But then Gideon Ward died.''%0a%0a''Gideon spent the better part of the next ten years in Atlanta before returning to his native Savannah.''[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_con.png%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://i10.photobucket.com/albums/a110/JustineNuara/EdwardCorey_zps85141023.jpg%0a[[Edward Corey]]   '''Carthian'''; ''Gideon holds tenancy in the Central District under this Carthian luminary.  Gideon makes no secret that he's one of Corey's men, but the relationship appears to be political/professional.''  %0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://i77.photobucket.com/albums/j52/Kitsuiko/WanWic%2520Character%2520Pictures/Michael01_zps8dd6d2a5.jpg%0a[[Michael Bertram Young|Michael Bertram-Young]]   '''Carthian'''; ''Kindred of similar standing are often at odds with each other, competing for what scraps of power still remain unclaimed.  If Gideon and Michael have such an arrangement, the two peers hide it well.''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://geraldparel.free.fr/wp-content/uploads/b_t5_machinegun_man1.jpg%0a[[Devon Van Der Metter]]   '''Carthian'''; ''Devon and Gideon share a Covenant and several hobbies.  Circumstances suggest they're collaborating on a number of projects now.''%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://i490.photobucket.com/albums/rr261/milokoplus/witch_zpse3ca558c.jpg%0a[[Ashildr de Haviland]]   '''Lady of the House'''; ''Gideon spends a suspicious amount of time at House Haviland on Wilmington Island, and would-be Harpies have whispered that he's up to something.  What that something is remains to be seen.''[[%3c%3c]]%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v490/Fenris_of_Siflige/goatfantastic_zps589d73a6.jpg%0a[[Goat]]   '''God Knows Why'''; ''Gideon seems to have an inexplicably high regard for Goat, and Gideon is one of the few people that Goat has not seen fit to fuck with, at least in public.  Why would a respectable Carthian with known sympathies for the Lancea Sanctum endure the company of a maniac Acolyte?''[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25lfloat width=70px%25http://i76.photobucket.com/albums/j17/rinijupiter/AARebekah/tumblr_mqg86m1ZFf1r3rfwmo1_500_zps629fb5b9.jpg%0a[[Rebekah Fuchs]]   '''God's Own Monster'''; ''Gideon's public interactions with Rebekah move fluidly between playful banter, paternal concern, and--most rare of all for Gideon--an almost humble deference.''[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_rph.png%0a*''Knight of the White Kamelia  (Mortals)'': %0aGideon maintains nothing so pretentious as an Invictus knighthood, but he has long been a knight of a different order: a circle of brothers dedicated to patriotism and purity.  Gideon keeps his secret closely, and interacts only at a distance, but it's possible others in respectable civic groups may feel his influence.%0a%0a*''Zealous Advocate (Vampires)'': %0aGideon offers counsel and advocacy to any who need it, at a modest price.  He will offer advice on the Requiem or on mortal society, negotiate disputes, and work to get Kindred out of trouble with the authorities.  Perhaps you've asked Gideon's help before, or perhaps you might need to soon.%0a%0a*''Hunt Club (Vampires, Mortals)'': %0aIn life and in death, hunting has long been a past-time for Gideon Ward.  As a vampire, Gideon has so many more opportunities for quarry.  Whether for animals or kine, Gideon invites his fellow Kindred out for sport, and enjoys making a game of it.  Going "fox" hunting on stolen steeds or playing a friendly game of "tag" with .22 rifles are all Gideon's ideas of a good time.  Gideon has his limits, though--it's gauche to kill kine for sport.  Maybe you want to go hunting with Gideon, or maybe you end up quarry.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/vtr/headers/vtr_q.png%0a''Adio Iman.'' -- [-(scrawled on her hand)-][[%3c%3c]]%0a''When we don't know who to hate, we hate ourselves.''-- [[Ashildr de Haviland]]%0a%0a''Those little white shorts suit him, strangely enough.'' -- [[Rebekah Fuchs]]%0a%0a''Drive your cart and your plow over the bones of the dead. The road of excess leads to the palace of wisdom.'' -- [[Players.MichaelBertramYoung|Michael Bertram-Young]]%0a%0a''You have to wonder about someone who treats Russian Roulette like a friendly game of Monopoly.'' -- [[AliceStepford|Lady Gourmand Alice Stepford]]%0a%0a''I want to make a motion we replace Judge with Professor.  Not to get philosophical but... Buddha said, One that does not feed nor create delusion, does so for enlightenment.  Thanks for dinner Prof. '' -- [[Devon Van Der Metter]]%0a%0a''I thought the Ventrue forgot how to be real vampires.  Then there's Gideon.'' -- [[Alexander]]%0a%0a''Thought's a luxury. Do you think the peasant sits and thinks of God and Democracy when he gets inside his mud hut at night? These words ring true to us Kindred as well. What good are thoughts, dogma, and ideals if we only use them to tear each other apart. A true statesman that understands the realities of our Requiem.'' -- [[Madison Gray]]%0a%0a''G looks like the Invictus but walks like the Movement.'' -- [[Hannah Dalton]]%0a%0a''Sooner or later every boy runs away to see the circus.'' -- [[Goat]]%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a(:include CityBook.VampireNavigationBar:)
